For Sandwich Spread, in small bowl, combine ingredients; set aside. For Sandwiches, season steak with Lawry's(R) Seasoned Salt and Lawry's(R) Seasoned Pepper. Brush onion with Olive Oil. Grill or broil steak and onion, turning once and brushing with steak sauce, until desired doneness. Cover steak loosely with aluminum foil; let stand 10 minutes. Thinly slice steak; set aside and keep warm. Evenly spread 1/4 cup sandwich spread on bottom of rolls. Top with lettuce, tomato, sliced steak and onion. Drizzle with remaining sauce, then top with remaining rolls.